In summary, this architecture uses **event sourcing** for an immutable audit log【24†L150-L158】, **domain-driven types** (F# DUs) for correctness, **TimescaleDB** for scalable time-series (with retention/compression to save ~90% of space【16†L145-L153】), and clear service boundaries (security, projection, ledger, reconciliation). All projected cash flows and actual transactions are stored with full versioning, so every number is traceable back to the source event. This meets the goals of auditability, lineage, accuracy, and performance laid out above.  

